Compare LET , VAR and CONST in the syntaxe of variable declaration on JS : 


var : 
    redeclare : Yes 
    Access Before declare : No => Undefined
    Note : 
        Every variable created by VAR, exemple ( var nameVariable = "Value" )
        put in the window object - check it in the console.
        

let : 
    redeclare : No => Error
    Access Before declare : No => Error

const : 
    redeclare : No => Error
    Access Before declare : No => Error
